node.text:
What a little editing can do! Swipe!➡️
.
Sometimes it’s really hard to see the potential in a picture😂 And that was definitely the case with this one… I didn’t know where to start, but when I hit the auto button it brightened up a bit and so I started tweaking a little more.👌
.
What basically turned out to be the problem with this picture were the color temperature, the tint and the saturation, who knew?!🤷‍♂️
.
Anyway, I’m really happy that this picture was shot in RAW because otherwise I would’ve been screwed.🤣
.
Quick question though: do you guys hit the auto-button every now and then?👀
.
Have a great Friday y’all!🤗
.
.
.

.

node.text:
Do you use Siri? I do and here are 3 Siri commands I use all the time!🔥
.
1. “What song is this?”🎼 Not that long ago Apple bought Shazam an app that could recognize songs🙌 And ever since then you are able to ask Siri what song is playing!😱
.
2. Calculator stuff🤓 I probably use this feature a bit to often, but you can ask Siri to calculate stuff for you! You can also ask her to convert currencies, measurements, etc.!👏
.
3. Intercom🎙 If you own a HomePod or HomePod mini you can use the intercom feature👌 You just say “Hey Siri, intercom [message]” and an intercom will be sent to everyone in your house!🤩 No more screaming up the staircase.😉
.
What are your favorite Siri commands? Drop them in the comments!👇
.
.
.
Follow: @appletodaynow 👨‍💻
.

The apple event invites are rumored to drop today!😱
.
At this event apple will likely launch the iPhone 13, Apple Watch series 7 and maybe even the AirPods 3.👏
.
This event will probably take place on the 14th of September online (that’s why the invites drop so late)👨‍💻 Apple’s past online events have been really well put together, so I’m excited to see all the smooth transition they made for us this time.👀
.
Show your hype for the iPhone event in the comments!🔥
.
.
.

node.text:
Do you use a smart home speaker?👀
.
I think it’s an essential part to a smart home as it can act as the hub of the house🔥 And I’ve been using the HomePod mini as that hub!🙌
.
I picked this particular smart speaker because it enables thread in my house (more on that later) and because it works really well with my apple ecosystem.👌
.
The sound is also amazing for its size!💥 We all know that Siri isn’t the brightest though, BUT I haven’t been able to ask her a question that she wasn’t able to answer🤷‍♂️ But that could just be me.😂
.
Do you guys own a smart speaker? Let me know in the comments!👏
.
.
.
Follow: @appletodaynow 🚀
.

node.text:
We could receive the apple event invites every minute now!😱
.
I’m really hyped for this event as a lot of products from a lot of different product categories could be announced!🤩 Anything from the new iPhone (which is pretty certain) to the new MacBook Pro’s (not so certain).🔥
.
So for the first time in years I actually have no clue what to really expect from this event and I quite like that😂 I do hope they announce the MacBooks soon though as I need a MacBook for college.👀
.
What new product are you most hyped for? Let me know in the comments and check out the poll in my story!🙌
.
.
.
Follow: @appletodaynow 👨‍💻
.

How to change the Apple Watch control center?😱
.
Simply go to the control center -> scroll all the way down -> hit “change” -> and start adding or moving buttons!🔥
.
I always like to keep my most used buttons like the flashlight and the do not disturb button at the top so I have quick access to them.👌
.
Do you guys change up your Apple Watch control center?⌚️ Let me know in the comments!👏
.

node.text:
The iPhone 13 is coming with a really exciting feature… and that’s LEO support!😱 But what is LEO?
.
LEO on the iPhone basically means that even when your phone is out of cellular range you’re still able to sent messages and receive phone calls.🙌
.
That’s because LEO (Low-earth-orbit) will connect the iPhone to a satellite which will make this possible🛰 This is really huge because it basically means that you can’t go out of range anymore.🤩
.
Are you hyped for this new feature? Let me know in the comments!🤙
.
.
.
Follow: @appletodaynow 👊
.

node.text:
Let’s do an update on my FCPX learning process!🔥
.
I feel like I’m getting to know the app better and better with each video that I make👌 And I think I’ve nailed down the basics, color grading and some speed ramping stuff!🤙 
.
I am also dabbling in making nice transitions which I think has been going really well👊 I got to thank @daniel.schiffer ‘s tutorials for that one though.🤣
.
I still got a lot to learn though😂 I’ve been struggling with finding the right titles and motion effects for example🤷‍♂️ I also don’t have a clue how LUTs work😅 If anyone wants to help, my DM’s are always open!😝
.
Have a great start of the week!✌️
.
.
.

node.text:
Project HomeKit: Part 2!😱
.
The @netatmo smoke detector is a great addition to my house!🤩 It isn’t a product that I use everyday (at least I hope so), but when I do use it this device could save me a lot of damage to my house!👌
.
It’s better than a regular smoke detector, because it will sent a notification to your phone as well as ring an alarm📣 So you’re notified no matter where you are, so you can act upon the situation sooner no matter where you are.👊
.
The link to the Netatmo smoke detector is in my bio, so go check it out!👏
.
.
.
